mgwport
========================================================================
This is mgwport, a revolutionary new method for building and maintaining
packages for the MinGW and MSYS platforms. It is based on the cygport
tool, from cygwin.

Runtime requirements:
  msys
  autoconf (both mingw and msys flavors)
  automake (both mingw and msys flavors)
  bash
  binutils
  bzip2
  coreutils
  cvs
  diffstat
  diffutils
  file
  gettext  (both mingw and msys flavors)
  grep
  gzip
  libiconv (both mingw and msys flavors)
  libtool  (both mingw and msys flavors)
  lndir
  make
  patch
  rsync
  sed
  tar
  unzip
  wget

Build requirements:
  mingw32-autoconf2.5
  mingw32-automake1.11
  msys-gawk
  msys-groff
  #help2man-1.36.4-10
  msys-make
  #robodoc-4.99.36-1
  msys-sed

Canonical website:
  http://sourceware.org/cygwinports/

Canonical download:
  http://downloads.sourceforge.net/cygwin-ports/

========================================================================

Build instructions:
  unpack mgwport-0.10.4-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  mgwport ./mgwport-0.10.4-X.mgwport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/mgwport-0.10.4-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/mgwport-0.10.4-X.tar.bz2

========================================================================

